      • receiveData

        public void receiveData(StatisticClassValue lowerValue,
                        StatisticClassValue upperValue,
                        int absoluteOccurence,
                        int currentViewIndex)
                 throws IllegalOverlapException,
                        IllegalBorderException,
                        java.lang.Exception
        This method is used to add or change statistical classes and their values.
        Parameters:
        lowerValue - StatisticClassValue object of the lower border value and bracket of the statistical class.
        upperValue - StatisticClassValue object of the upper border value and bracket of the statistical class.
        absoluteOccurence - Number of data points in the handled statistical class.
        currentViewIndex - Current Integer index of the handled statistical class.
        Throws:
        IllegalOverlapException - Exception due to overlapping borders with one or multiple other statistical classes.
        IllegalBorderException - Exception due to illegal borders.
